description:
Add to methods/mod.rs (or a new methods/patch.rs):

pub enum Patch<T> { Keep, Set(T), Clear }
impl<T> Default for Patch<T> { fn default() -> Self { Patch::Keep } }
impl<T> From<T> for Patch<T> { fn from(v: T) -> Self { Patch::Set(v) } }

Serde: must NOT derive Serialize/Deserialize on Patch itself — the to-JSON logic lives in the method implementation which conditionally inserts/omits the key. Add a helper method Patch::into_json(key, map) that inserts only when not Keep.
